g.text: UML Diagram: Class DimensionalDataStructure in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.
- The arrows of the inheritance tree are

a.title: ― DimensionGroup: Collection of dimensions that can be reused across multiple dimensional structures.
a.xlink:title: ― DimensionGroup: Collection of dimensions that can be reused across multiple dimensional structures.

a.title: ― DataPoint: Container for an instance value.
a.xlink:title: ― DataPoint: Container for an instance value.

a.title: ― DataSet: Organized collection of data based on keys.
a.xlink:title: ― DataSet: Organized collection of data based on keys.

a.title: ― DataStructure: Data organization based on reusable data structure components.
a.xlink:title: ― DataStructure: Data organization based on reusable data structure components.

a.title: ― ForeignKey: Role of a set of data structure components for content referencing purposes
a.xlink:title: ― ForeignKey: Role of a set of data structure components for content referencing purposes

a.title: ― AttributeComponent: Role given to a represented variable in the context of a data structure to qualify observations or provide other types of supplementary information.
a.xlink:title: ― AttributeComponent: Role given to a represented variable in the context of a data structure to qualify observations or provide other types of supplementary information.

a.title: ― ComponentPosition: Indexes the components in a data structure using integers with a position indicated by incrementing upward from 0 or 1.
a.xlink:title: ― ComponentPosition: Indexes the components in a data structure using integers with a position indicated by incrementing upward from 0 or 1.

a.title: ― RepresentedVariable: Conceptual variable with a substantive value domain specified.
a.xlink:title: ― RepresentedVariable: Conceptual variable with a substantive value domain specified.

a.title: ― DataStructureComponent: Role given to a represented variable in the context of a data structure.
a.xlink:title: ― DataStructureComponent: Role given to a represented variable in the context of a data structure.

a.title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.
a.xlink:title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.

a.title: ― PairedControlledVocabularyEntry: A tightly bound pair of items from an external controlled vocabulary. The extent property describes the extent to which the parent term applies for the specific case.
a.xlink:title: ― PairedControlledVocabularyEntry: A tightly bound pair of items from an external controlled vocabulary. The extent property describes the extent to which the parent term applies for the specific case.

a.title: ― SpecializationRole: Specific roles played by represented variables in terms of time, geography, and other concepts which are important for the harmonization and integration of data.
a.xlink:title: ― SpecializationRole: Specific roles played by represented variables in terms of time, geography, and other concepts which are important for the harmonization and integration of data.

a.title: ― isDefinedBy: Data structure component is defined by zero to one represented variable.
a.xlink:title: ― isDefinedBy: Data structure component is defined by zero to one represented variable.
